<div>
<h3 class="bac">Summary</h3>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Locations London  &amp; Chester</li>
	<li>2-year rotational programme</li>
	<li>On track for a minimum of a 2:1 degree classification (or equivalent), ideally from Engineering or Computer Science</li>
	<li>Fluency in English</li>
</ul>
<p class="bac">Enterprise Change, Technology  &amp; Operations (ECT &amp;O) facilitate Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America Merrill Lynch customer, client and employee requirements through the implementation of technology, systems, call centres and various tools and channels.</p>
<p class="bac">The programme is designed to provide candidates with the opportunity to prepare for future leadership positions in technology and business technology groups within ECT &amp;O based on their academic experience, background and skills sets demonstrated throughout the interview process.</p>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif">Overview</h2>
<div>
<p class="bac nobr">As an Analyst, you will:</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Participate in design, development and implementation of complex systems/applications often using new technologies in support of business goals</li>
	<li>Analyse, track and troubleshoot performance of an assigned system or network to ensure that all information processing and delivery requirements are met</li>
	<li>Provide project management support relating to process improvements in technology</li>
	<li>Collaborate on global projects that contribute to business success and next-generation advances</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif">Training</h2>
<div>
<p class="bac nobr">Training will include:</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Monthly education events, where you will team up with fellow ECT &amp;O Industrial Placements, Graduate and Summer Interns to interact face to face with multiple line of business representatives, senior leaders and technology partners</li>
	<li>Access to the Associate Development Centre, an internally developed intranet site providing structured programs with competency-based learning paths and career planning process tools</li>
	<li>Invaluable hands on experience of day to day operation, support and development within a global enterprise environment</li>
	<li>You will also be assigned a mentor from the ECT &amp;O leadership team to assist with personal development</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif">Qualifications</h2>
<div>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>A passion and interest in technology</li>
	<li>A Bachelor&#39;s, Master&#39;s, or Doctorate degree in Computer Science/Engineering, Mathematics, Physics, or a related science or engineering discipline will be relevant</li>
	<li>An ability to work in a fast paced environment whilst multi tasking  &amp; interacting with a wide variety of people</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

